            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><space quantity="9" unit="chars"/><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="ink"/>ragland castle</head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <!--Ruskin's hand persists in print and ink from the <handShift/> above to the first <handShift/> in the line below-in which an unknown person (i.e. "HANDX") has marked an "x" above the "a" in "are." The
                    <handShift/> following this intervention restores the ownership of the hand to Ruskin's. While it is logical to assume that <handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27"/> should/would restore both the ownership AND character of the
                    hand, TEI P5 fails to make clear whether <handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27"/> would merely signal a change in the @scribe and no other, pre-existing attributes (i.e. @script and @medium). Consequently, in the line below,
                    the @script and @medium that should be associated with Ruskin's hand following the intervention by "HANDX" are explicitly re-stated. Ruskin's hand-in print and ink-persits from this point through the witness to the end
                    of MS III-or until the next <handShift/>.-->
                    <l><hi rend="caps, doubleletter">O</hi><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses2.php#DOUBLELETTER"/> <hi rend="smallcaps"><placeName corresp="#RAGLAN">ragland</placeName></hi> beauty as you <add place="above"><space quantity="25" unit="chars"/><handShift new="#HANDX" script="print" medium="pencil"/><metamark function="unknown">&#x00D7;</metamark></add><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="ink"/>ar<hi rend="overwriting">e</hi><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses.php#CROSS"/></l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>ruined arches towers and views</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>not ruined views but fine ones</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>your gothic arches and your falling towers.</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>with keystones moats and drawbridges<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses.php#MOATS"/></l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>your mice&#x2010;house moss and burnt up grass<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses.php#MOSS"/></l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>for mice to pull and line their falling dwellings</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>your spiral towers<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses.php#SPIRALTOWERS"/> and holes for mice to live in</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>your dungeons splits<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="ragland_castle_glosses.php#SPLITGLOSS"/> and drawbridges</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>battlements courts and lodges</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>so <placeName corresp="#RAGLAN">ragland</placeName> as I have described you</l>
                    <l><space quantity="1" unit="chars"/>I must take leave of you</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
